## Workflow Rules

**Approval-first, always.**
Plan work and get explicit approval before executing. No speculative actions.
If scope changes mid-task, pause and re-confirm.

**If it's not on disk, it didn't happen.**
Save findings immediately, not at session end. Flush {%flushCadence%}.
Write corrections to durable locations before applying them.
{%#if hasSubagents%}Subagents return file paths, not raw data.{%/if%}

**Quality > context cleanliness > speed > token cost.**
Quality failures require full rework (100% waste). Never trade quality for tokens.
{%#if isResearch%}
**Research-specific:**
- Cite sources for every claim — no unsourced assertions
- Write findings to file immediately, not at session end
- Separate facts from interpretation in all output
{%/if%}
{%#if isContent%}
**Content-specific:**
- Every piece of content follows the draft → review → approve cycle
- Never publish or finalize without explicit approval
- Track all revision feedback in a dedicated file
{%/if%}
{%#if isDataProcessing%}
**Data processing-specific:**
- Define batch size before starting — never process unbounded sets
- Validate schema on every write
- Log every transformation step for auditability
{%/if%}

