## Context Discipline

- Flush working state to file {%flushCadence%}
{%#if hasSubagents%}- Subagents write output to `tmp/{task}/{name}.json`; return one-line receipt
- Main session reads subagent files ONLY if needed for the next step
- Never hold raw batch results in conversation — write to disk first
{%/if%}- Before batch work: write execution plan to file (survives context loss)

---
{%#if sessionHandoff%}
## Session Handoff Checklist

Run this at every session end (mandatory, not optional):

1. Save all work to SSOT files
2. Sync derived files (rebuild from SSOTs)
3. SSOT integrity check (no duplicates, no stale data)
4. Update progress tracker
5. Write next-session plan (with pre-execution hooks listed)
6. Launch QC on work done this session

